A very pleasant surprise is this beautiful Notre-Dame de Clignancourt church, located on a “small town” style square with its town hall, church and riding school.  The interior is neat, beautiful and quiet. We feel that it is a place of prayer with its numerous devotional statues, and the chapel of the Blessed Sacrament in the apse.  This church lives, it is felt and it is a pleasure. A must see

The visit is free and the place is full of charm and history..very beautiful church located in the heart of the eighteenth arrondissement of Paris, opposite the town hall and a stone's throw from the Jules Joffrin metro station.

This is a place that is dear to the painter Utrillo and his mother, Suzanne Valadon. Although there are many attractions such as the beautiful Mary Chapelle and stained glass windows, there are very few tourists as it is located on the edge of the 18th arrondissement. There's a quiet solemnity that draws you in, making you feel like you'll lose track of time and indulge in self-reflection.

caption: Very beautiful church located just opposite the 18th century town hall and at the metro exit. The church is very large, not very new, that’s what makes it so charming! It is very beautiful, we find our lady of Lourdes, our lady of Fatima, Saint Anthony of Padua, Saint Thérèse of Lisieux...  Small prayers are available right next to each saint. This is a very good idea.  I really like this church.
Very surprising, it is magnificent, the visit is free and full of beautiful surprises The serenity of this place is impressive.
Very beautiful church, statue of Saint Rita and other statues, absolutely worth visiting. Very beautiful place of prayer. Saint Rita pray for us THANKS
It's noisy outside the church, but once you step inside, the atmosphere is different. Sometimes people come to pray. I stayed in this church for about an hour and I also prayed.

Built on the square, formerly Sainte Euphrasie, now Place Jules-Joffrin, the first stone of which was blessed by Cardinal Morlot, Archbishop of Paris and laid by Baron Hausman on May 2, 1859, and it was inaugurated on October 29, 1863.  To be discovered in all humility in the lively district of the 18th century town hall.  .

Open from 9 a.m. to 7:30 p.m. At the final stop of the Montmartrobus and No. 80 bus routes is this large church influenced by Tuscan art from the mid-19th century, when Paris was expanding.  The glass windows with their depictions of saints from a workshop from 1923-44 shine like precious stones. Trinity and Mary in the choir were only created in 1970. Dominicans celebrate Holy Mass here. A large church interior that lifts the heart to the Lord and to his mother Mary.
Church worth visiting. 5 minutes for a prayer doesn't hurt
Clean, calm and soothing. Between the Jules Joffrin and rue Hermel metro station. Free entry.
Beautiful Sunday mass at 11am, with music and liturgy filled with the Holy Spirit.

One of the rare churches where I go with pleasure to attend mass. A place of prayer and liturgical chants brilliantly led by competent faithful, assisted by a very good organist. I really have the feeling of belonging to a vibrant community, thanks to the team of priests.

Coming to attend the Palm Sunday service on this Sunday, April 2, 2023, I found this place magnificent. I had already been there to visit it, at the time, in the middle of the covid-19 period and I found it quite remarkable. I recommend a full visit outside of religious services of course.
Beautiful church, a haven of peace. The stained glass windows are beautiful.
A large parish full of life. People of all ages at the celebrations. Very nice.

It is a beautiful Church ⛪ from the outside and even inside with these beautiful sculptures, paintings and stained glass windows. I can understand that some churches do not have enough budget to maintain the walls, statues etc. But what I can't accept. It is the lack of hygiene in a Temple. Just at the entrance, on the side of the old baptistery, the floor is dirty, there are traces of dust and plaster. The curtain which hides the frescoes are filled with wax... The statues are also dirty, We can see this because people touch the statues and they change color. Maybe the manager is overwhelmed? Or too old? Could we call on volunteers? I would be happy to lend a hand and make this temple shine with our love and care... Sorry if you find it a bit harsh.. And respects to this parish and these leaders.

I love this parish...the architecture is magnificent...the setting too...a little dark but idyllic...several masses per day and rosaries every day in groups...the parish priests and priests are very welcoming. .. The atmosphere inspires prayer and always makes you want to come back...
Very beautiful church

Church not very busy so it's better... Remove the carousel from the square, and the church will be prettier... Even the redone square they put it back... A little less tramp anyway... except when there is the soup kitchen at the presbitaire rue Hermel next to the crèche...
Church opposite the town hall of the 18th arrondissement of Paris, adoration of the holy sacrament every day, recent acquisition of a copy of the Child Jesus statuette of Prague.

I am outraged. How, for so many years, can we allow this lack of respect towards the French and the Catholic religion by hiding the facade of the Notre Dame de Clignancourt Church with a merry-go-round? I want to find Place Jules Joffrin like before where the exit from the Church faces the Town Hall!
